as nothing new when Mayor Giuliani was unable to ban sales by immigrant mobile food vendors. The Guide takes us to the place where the Dutch tried to ban street side sales by Scottish peddlers 350 years ago, and where the great Fiorello La Guardia banned most of the pushcart salesmen at midcentury. But Kamil and Wakin are not nostalgists or preservationists. Instead, their historical tours connect today's city with the snapshots of yesterday, blending social and cultural history with the evolution of different ethnic and cultural communities. The Big Onion Guide includes ten walking tours, plus a 5-borough driving tour, peppered with informative sidebars, illustrations, and photos from the collection at the New-York Historical Society.Visit the Big Onion Guide to New York City site at www.nyupress.org/bigonion  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aHistoric siteszNew York (State)zNew YorkvGuidebooks. 0aWalkingzNew York (State)zNew YorkvGuidebooks. 7aTravel / United States / Northeast / Middle Atlantic (NJ, NY, PA).2bisacsh  aApple.  aCity.  aLong.  aOnion.  aYork.  abefore.  acalled.  adubbed.  aknew.  athose.1 aJackson, Kenneth T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJackson, Kenneth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKamil, Seth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWakin, Eric, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWakin, Eric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070644440uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479800131.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479800131423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/97